EMR stands for Elastic Map Reduce
EMR helps creating Hadoop Clusters BIG DATA to analyze and proccess vast amount of data
HBadoop / BIG = EMR
The cluster can made of hundreds of EC2
EMR comes bundled with Apache Spark, Hbase, Presto
EMR takes care of all the provisioning and confiigurations
Auto scaling and integratated with spot instances
Use cases: Data proccessing, machine learning, web indexing BIG DATA
------------

nODE tYPES AND pURCHASING

Master node: manage the cluster, coordinate, manage health - long running
Core node: Run tasks and storee data - long running
Task node: just to run tasks - usually spot
Purchasing options:
  on demand: reliable, predictable, wont be terminated
  Reserved (min 1 year): cost savings EMR will automatically use
  Spot instances: cheaper, can be terminated, less reliable
Can have long running cluster or transient cluster

